{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015vpiGLDUpfSYkxW5vTRYpo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{{define \"content\"}}\n     2→<h1>Projects</h1>\n     3→{{if .Projects}}\n     4→<div class=\"project-cards\">\n     5→    {{range .Projects}}\n     6→    <div class=\"project-card\">\n     7→        <div class=\"project-header\">\n     8→            <span class=\"health-dot health-{{healthColor .Health.Status}}\" title=\"{{.Health.Status}}\"></span>\n     9→            <a href=\"/projects/{{.Label}}\" class=\"project-name\">{{.Label}}</a>\n    10→        </div>\n    11→        <div class=\"project-stats\">\n    12→            <div class=\"stat\">\n    13→                <span class=\"stat-value\">{{.Health.Passed}}/{{.Health.Total}}</span>\n    14→                <span class=\"stat-label\">recent passed</span>\n    15→            </div>\n    16→            <div class=\"stat\">\n    17→                <span class=\"stat-value\">{{.ActiveCount}}</span>\n    18→                <span class=\"stat-label\">active</span>\n    19→            </div>\n    20→        </div>\n    21→        <div class=\"run-history\">\n    22→            {{range .RecentRuns}}\n    23→            <span class=\"run-dot run-dot-{{.State}}\" title=\"{{.ID}}: {{.State}}\"></span>\n    24→            {{end}}\n    25→        </div>\n    26→        <div class=\"project-actions\">\n    27→            <a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">View Runs</a>\n    28→            <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" onclick=\"triggerOrchestrator('{{.Label}}', '{{.Dir}}')\">Trigger Orchestrator</button>\n    29→        </div>\n    30→    </div>\n    31→    {{end}}\n    32→</div>\n    33→{{else}}\n    34→<p class=\"empty\">No projects yet. Start a workflow run to see projects here.</p>\n    35→{{end}}\n    36→{{end}}\n    37→\n    38→{{define \"scripts\"}}\n    39→<script>\n    40→function triggerOrchestrator(label, dir) {\n    41→    var btn = event.target;\n    42→    btn.disabled = true;\n    43→    btn.textContent = 'Triggering...';\n    44→    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(label) + '/trigger', {method: 'POST'})\n    45→        .then(function(r) {\n    46→            if (r.ok) {\n    47→                r.json().then(function(data) {\n    48→                    if (data.dispatched > 0) {\n    49→                        btn.textContent = 'Dispatched ' + data.dispatched;\n    50→                    } else {\n    51→                        btn.textContent = 'No tasks ready';\n    52→                    }\n    53→                    setTimeout(function() {\n    54→                        btn.disabled = false;\n    55→                        btn.textContent = 'Trigger Orchestrator';\n    56→                    }, 2000);\n    57→                });\n    58→            } else {\n    59→                r.json().then(function(data) {\n    60→                    btn.textContent = 'Failed: ' + (data.error || 'unknown');\n    61→                }).catch(function() {\n    62→                    btn.textContent = 'Failed';\n    63→                });\n    64→                setTimeout(function() {\n    65→                    btn.disabled = false;\n    66→                    btn.textContent = 'Trigger Orchestrator';\n    67→                }, 4000);\n    68→            }\n    69→        })\n    70→        .catch(function() {\n    71→            btn.textContent = 'Failed';\n    72→            setTimeout(function() {\n    73→                btn.disabled = false;\n    74→                btn.textContent = 'Trigger Orchestrator';\n    75→            }, 2000);\n    76→        });\n    77→}\n    78→</script>\n    79→{{end}}\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MfD86qGaYCESVqUTMLNaVG","session_id":"503a9c6b-ea73-4496-a067-8391d86da200","uuid":"53482dbe-e58f-4d76-913e-84f4461e0ef5"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a58b73e374a1feaa1","tool_use_id":"toolu_01MfD86qGaYCESVqUTMLNaVG","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore workflow view code","usage":{"total_tokens":59344,"tool_uses":26,"duration_ms":35308},"uuid":"de1b20f8-a4c8-4e76-a603-6a3fd3f72272","session_id":"503a9c6b-ea73-4496-a067-8391d86da200"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MfD86qGaYCESVqUTMLNaVG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the workflow view. Let me create a final summary document with all the findings:\n\n## Summary: Workflow View Architecture in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase and identified all the components related to the workflow view (project page where you can click on steps). Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Web UI / Frontend Code Location**\n- **Main handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (36,645 bytes)\n- **HTML templates:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n  - `project_detail.html` - The workflow view page\n  - `projects.html` - Project overview page\n  - `run_detail.html` - Run details page\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page\n  - `layout.html` - Base layout template\n- **CSS styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 2. **How Steps Display Prompt Filenames vs File Contents**\n\nThe handler has two key mechanisms:\n\n**A. Displaying Step Definitions (Workflow View - project_detail.html)**\n- Handler: `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1058-1132)\n- Returns JSON with step configuration including:\n  - Step name\n  - Step type (agent, script)\n  - Results\n  - **Config map** containing references like `\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\"`\n- The frontend displays the **filename** (not contents) in the DAG visualization\n\n**B. Loading Step Content (Drawer Panel - project_detail.html)**\n- Handler: `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1134-1199)\n- Called when user clicks on a step in the DAG\n- Returns the actual **file contents** based on the step config:\n  - If `step.Config[\"prompt\"]` exists: reads the file from disk (line 1177-1182)\n  - If `step.Config[\"command\"]` exists: returns the command text directly (line 1184-1186)\n  - If `step.Config[\"script\"]` exists: reads the file or returns inline text (line 1188-1196)\n\n### 3. **API Endpoints for Step Details and File Contents**\n\nKey endpoints in the handler:\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Handler | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|---------|\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | GET | `handleAPIWorkflows()` | Get all workflows with step definitions |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | GET | `handleAPIStepContent()` | Get step content (prompt or script) |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info` | GET | `handleAPIProjectInfo()` | Get project info including prompt file history |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` | GET | `handleAPIPromptDiff()` | Get git diff for a specific prompt commit |\n| `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` | GET | `handleAPIStepOutput()` | Get execution output from a run |\n\n### 4. **Handler/Template/Component Code for Workflow View**\n\n**Main Project Detail View Handler:**\n- `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 835-861) - Serves the HTML page\n- Routes to: `GET /projects/{name}`\n\n**Workflow Panel JavaScript (in project_detail.html, lines 141-298):**\n- `loadWorkflows()` - Fetches workflow definitions from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n- `showWorkflow(idx)` - Renders SVG DAG with step nodes and wires\n- `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)` - Opens side drawer with step details\n  - Fetches step content from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n  - Displays step metadata (type, results, config)\n  - Shows file contents in a `<pre>` block\n\n**Key UI Components:**\n1. **Workflow Panel** - Three sections:\n   - Orchestrator Control (enable/disable, concurrency)\n   - Project Info (Docker image, version, prompt files with git history)\n   - Workflows (tabbed interface showing DAG)\n\n2. **Step Drawer** - Slides in from right side showing:\n   - Step name in header\n   - Step metadata (type, results)\n   - Config keys (prompt filename, command, etc.)\n   - Content preview (loaded via fetch from API)\n\n3. **DAG Visualization** - SVG rendering with:\n   - Clickable step nodes (light bulb emoji for agent, document emoji for script)\n   - Connection wires with result labels\n   - Terminal nodes (done/abort)\n\n### 5. **Data Flow for Workflow View**\n\n```\nUser clicks /projects/{projectName}\n    ↓\nhandleProjectDetail() renders HTML\n    ↓\nproject_detail.html loads via JavaScript:\n    1. Orchestrator status: /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\n    2. Project info: /api/projects/{name}/info\n    3. Workflows: /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n    ↓\nFrontend displays DAG with step nodes\n    ↓\nUser clicks on a step node\n    ↓\nopenDrawer(workflowName, stepName)\n    ↓\nFetch /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n    ↓\nHandler reads from step.Config[\"prompt\"] file\n    ↓\nDisplay file contents in drawer\n\n```\n\n### 6. **Domain Models**\n\n**Step structure** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 21-26):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string              // Step identifier\n    Type    StepType            // \"agent\", \"script\", \"workflow\"\n    Results []string            // Possible outcomes\n    Config  map[string]string   // e.g., {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/fix.md\"}\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow structure** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 52-59):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string            // Workflow name\n    Steps     map[string]*Step  // All steps in workflow\n    Wiring    []Wire            // Connections between steps\n    EntryStep string            // Starting step\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **CSS Styling for Workflow View**\n\nKey CSS classes in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`:\n- `.dag-svg` - SVG container for DAG\n- `.dag-node` - Step nodes (clickable)\n- `.dag-node-rect` - Node styling\n- `.dag-edge` - Connection lines\n- `.dag-edge-label` - Result labels on connections\n- `.drawer` - Side panel (slides in from right)\n- `.drawer-body` - Content area with `pre` tags\n- `.panel` - Container panels (Orchestrator, Info, Workflows)\n- `.tab-bar` / `.tab-btn` - Tab interface for multiple workflows\n\nAll code is located at the absolute paths listed above in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a58b73e374a1feaa1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60930\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 35312</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"503a9c6b-ea73-4496-a067-8391d86da200","uuid":"294e92a8-96b0-48f0-a104-8ca8a8479769","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand the workflow view in the project page. I need to find:\n\n1. The web UI / frontend code that renders the workflow view (project page where you click on steps)\n2. How steps display prompt filenames vs file contents\n3. Any API endpoints that serve step details or file contents\n4. The relevant handler/template/component code for the workflow view\n\nLook in directories like cmd/, internal/adapters/, internal/ports/, and any web/template/frontend directories. Search for terms like \"workflow\", \"step\", \"prompt\", \"project page\", \"file contents\", \"template\", \"handler\", \"web\", \"http\", \"server\".\n\nBe very thorough - check all potential locations for web UI code.","agentId":"a58b73e374a1feaa1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the workflow view. Let me create a final summary document with all the findings:\n\n## Summary: Workflow View Architecture in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase and identified all the components related to the workflow view (project page where you can click on steps). Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **Web UI / Frontend Code Location**\n- **Main handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (36,645 bytes)\n- **HTML templates:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`\n  - `project_detail.html` - The workflow view page\n  - `projects.html` - Project overview page\n  - `run_detail.html` - Run details page\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page\n  - `layout.html` - Base layout template\n- **CSS styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 2. **How Steps Display Prompt Filenames vs File Contents**\n\nThe handler has two key mechanisms:\n\n**A. Displaying Step Definitions (Workflow View - project_detail.html)**\n- Handler: `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1058-1132)\n- Returns JSON with step configuration including:\n  - Step name\n  - Step type (agent, script)\n  - Results\n  - **Config map** containing references like `\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/implement.md\"`\n- The frontend displays the **filename** (not contents) in the DAG visualization\n\n**B. Loading Step Content (Drawer Panel - project_detail.html)**\n- Handler: `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1134-1199)\n- Called when user clicks on a step in the DAG\n- Returns the actual **file contents** based on the step config:\n  - If `step.Config[\"prompt\"]` exists: reads the file from disk (line 1177-1182)\n  - If `step.Config[\"command\"]` exists: returns the command text directly (line 1184-1186)\n  - If `step.Config[\"script\"]` exists: reads the file or returns inline text (line 1188-1196)\n\n### 3. **API Endpoints for Step Details and File Contents**\n\nKey endpoints in the handler:\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Handler | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|---------|\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | GET | `handleAPIWorkflows()` | Get all workflows with step definitions |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | GET | `handleAPIStepContent()` | Get step content (prompt or script) |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info` | GET | `handleAPIProjectInfo()` | Get project info including prompt file history |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` | GET | `handleAPIPromptDiff()` | Get git diff for a specific prompt commit |\n| `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` | GET | `handleAPIStepOutput()` | Get execution output from a run |\n\n### 4. **Handler/Template/Component Code for Workflow View**\n\n**Main Project Detail View Handler:**\n- `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 835-861) - Serves the HTML page\n- Routes to: `GET /projects/{name}`\n\n**Workflow Panel JavaScript (in project_detail.html, lines 141-298):**\n- `loadWorkflows()` - Fetches workflow definitions from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n- `showWorkflow(idx)` - Renders SVG DAG with step nodes and wires\n- `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)` - Opens side drawer with step details\n  - Fetches step content from `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`\n  - Displays step metadata (type, results, config)\n  - Shows file contents in a `<pre>` block\n\n**Key UI Components:**\n1. **Workflow Panel** - Three sections:\n   - Orchestrator Control (enable/disable, concurrency)\n   - Project Info (Docker image, version, prompt files with git history)\n   - Workflows (tabbed interface showing DAG)\n\n2. **Step Drawer** - Slides in from right side showing:\n   - Step name in header\n   - Step metadata (type, results)\n   - Config keys (prompt filename, command, etc.)\n   - Content preview (loaded via fetch from API)\n\n3. **DAG Visualization** - SVG rendering with:\n   - Clickable step nodes (light bulb emoji for agent, document emoji for script)\n   - Connection wires with result labels\n   - Terminal nodes (done/abort)\n\n### 5. **Data Flow for Workflow View**\n\n```\nUser clicks /projects/{projectName}\n    ↓\nhandleProjectDetail() renders HTML\n    ↓\nproject_detail.html loads via JavaScript:\n    1. Orchestrator status: /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\n    2. Project info: /api/projects/{name}/info\n    3. Workflows: /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n    ↓\nFrontend displays DAG with step nodes\n    ↓\nUser clicks on a step node\n    ↓\nopenDrawer(workflowName, stepName)\n    ↓\nFetch /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\n    ↓\nHandler reads from step.Config[\"prompt\"] file\n    ↓\nDisplay file contents in drawer\n\n```\n\n### 6. **Domain Models**\n\n**Step structure** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 21-26):\n```go\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string              // Step identifier\n    Type    StepType            // \"agent\", \"script\", \"workflow\"\n    Results []string            // Possible outcomes\n    Config  map[string]string   // e.g., {\"prompt\": \".cloche/prompts/fix.md\"}\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow structure** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, lines 52-59):\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string            // Workflow name\n    Steps     map[string]*Step  // All steps in workflow\n    Wiring    []Wire            // Connections between steps\n    EntryStep string            // Starting step\n}\n```\n\n### 7. **CSS Styling for Workflow View**\n\nKey CSS classes in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`:\n- `.dag-svg` - SVG container for DAG\n- `.dag-node` - Step nodes (clickable)\n- `.dag-node-rect` - Node styling\n- `.dag-edge` - Connection lines\n- `.dag-edge-label` - Result labels on connections\n- `.drawer` - Side panel (slides in from right)\n- `.drawer-body` - Content area with `pre` tags\n- `.panel` - Container panels (Orchestrator, Info, Workflows)\n- `.tab-bar` / `.tab-btn` - Tab interface for multiple workflows\n\nAll code is located at the absolute paths listed above in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/`."}],"totalDurationMs":35312,"totalTokens":60930,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1204,"cache_read_input_tokens":58035,"output_tokens":1686,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1204},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
