{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012PJi1w256pqYwUp1Xc57sa","type":"tool_result","content":"820:func (h *Handler) resolveProjectDir(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) (string, string, bool) {\n821-\tlabel := r.PathValue(\"name\")\n822-\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n823-\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n824-\tfor dir, l := range labels {\n825-\t\tif l == label {\n826-\t\t\treturn dir, label, true\n827-\t\t}\n828-\t}\n829-\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n830-\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n831-\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"project not found\"})\n832-\treturn \"\", \"\", false\n833-}\n834-\n835-func (h *Handler) handleProjectDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n836-\tdir, label, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n837-\tif !ok {\n838-\t\treturn\n839-\t}\n840-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"503a9c6b-ea73-4496-a067-8391d86da200","uuid":"f5f9d1a5-1e3a-4aaa-8cff-a4c4e53a9e88","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"820:func (h *Handler) resolveProjectDir(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) (string, string, bool) {\n821-\tlabel := r.PathValue(\"name\")\n822-\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n823-\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n824-\tfor dir, l := range labels {\n825-\t\tif l == label {\n826-\t\t\treturn dir, label, true\n827-\t\t}\n828-\t}\n829-\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n830-\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n831-\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"project not found\"})\n832-\treturn \"\", \"\", false\n833-}\n834-\n835-func (h *Handler) handleProjectDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n836-\tdir, label, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n837-\tif !ok {\n838-\t\treturn\n839-\t}\n840-","numLines":21}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014c5UXEW5Fezyx4xzHHYGRz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the route is registered. The `handleAPIStepContent` handler looks correct - it finds the workflow, finds the step, and reads the file content from disk. Let me investigate what might be going wrong.\n\nLooking at the frontend code more carefully:\n\n```javascript\nfetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/workflows/' + encodeURIComponent(workflowName) + '/steps/' + encodeURIComponent(stepName) + '/content')\n    .then(function(r) { if (r.ok) return r.text(); return ''; })\n    .then(function(text) {\n\n\n```\n\nThe frontend is making a fetch request to the content endpoint and handling the response. Then it's taking that text and inserting it into the drawer element, escaping HTML entities so the content displays as plain text in a `<pre>` tag, or showing a fallback message if there's no content. This all looks right to me. Let me trace through the backend handler to see where things might be breaking down.\n\nI'm checking the `handleAPIStepContent` function and I see it's extracting the workflow and step names from the URL path. Then it's looking up the step configuration and checking if there's a `prompt` field. If there is, it tries to read that file relative to the project directory. So if the project is at `/home/user/myproject` and the prompt path is `.cloche/prompts/implement.md`, it would attempt to read from `/home/user/myproject/.cloche/prompts/implement.md`. That seems like the right approach, but something's going wrong there.\n\nLet me trace through how the project directory is being resolved. The `dir` comes from `h.store.ListProjects`, so I need to understand how projects are actually stored and whether the daemon is running in the right context to access those file paths. Also, looking at the frontend code, it's displaying the filename from `step.config[k]` directly in the UI, which explains why the user sees the filename but not the actual contents—the frontend is just showing the config value as-is rather than loading the file content from the API. I need to understand how the DSL parser extracts and stores file paths in the step configuration to figure out why the content isn't loading properly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":426,"cache_read_input_tokens":24807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":426},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"503a9c6b-ea73-4496-a067-8391d86da200","uuid":"8650592b-b098-4e1e-9c7d-aa5095c33743"}
