Content` function reads the actual content:\n```go\nif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, prompt))\n    // Returns error if prompt contains \"file(...)\" instead of extracting path\n}\n```\n\n**Important:** The handler code attempts to read paths directly without parsing the `file(...)` wrapper, suggesting either:\n1. The paths should be stored without the `file()` wrapper, OR\n2. There's post-processing of the config values elsewhere\n\n### 5. Test Evidence\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`:\n\n**Line 42:** Shows that `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")` is stored as-is:\n```go\nassert.Equal(t, `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")`, code.Config[\"prompt\"])\n```\n\n**Lines 53-68:** Minimal workflow test shows `run` commands are stored as plain strings:\n```go\nassert.Equal(t, \"make test && make lint\", check.Config[\"run\"])\n```\n\n### 6. Step Type Inference\n\nSteps are automatically typed based on which config field is present (lines 166-195):\n- **StepTypeAgent**: has \"prompt\" field\n- **StepTypeScript**: has \"run\" field  \n- **StepTypeWorkflow**: has \"workflow_name\" field\n\nA step can have exactly ONE of these; having multiple or none causes a parse error.\n\n### 7. Container Configuration\n\nSub-blocks are supported and stored with dot notation (lines 211-220):\n```go\ncontainer {\n    image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal.example.com\"]\n}\n```\n\nStored as:\n- `container.image` → `cloche/agent:latest`\n- `container.network_allow` → `docs.python.org,internal.example.com` (comma-separated)\n\n### 8. Sample Workflow Format\n\nFrom `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche`:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"go test ./... 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### 9. Web Handler Integration\n\nIn `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`, the API endpoint `handleAPIStepContent` (lines 1134-1199) uses the stored config values to resolve actual file paths. The handler assumes prompt values are **relative to the project directory** (`filepath.Join(dir, prompt)`).\n\nThis mismatch with `file(\"...\")` syntax suggests the DSL parser should extract the path from within the function call, or the handler should parse it.\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Storage location**: `Step.Config[\"fieldname\"]` (map of strings)\n- **Prompt paths**: Stored as complete `file(\"path\")` function calls\n- **Script/run commands**: Stored as plain command strings\n- **Resolution**: Happens at runtime in handlers, using relative paths from project root\n- **Key files**: Parser at `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, handlers at `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":22590,"totalTokens":59435,"totalToolUseCount":16,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29739,"cache_read_input_tokens":28324,"output_tokens":1365,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":29739},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
